figure_1.title: Figure 1.
figure_1.caption: Interview guide of theory-based core questions for focus groups analyzing professional identity formation of undergraduate students in health promotion and prevention.

figure_2.title: Figure 2.
figure_2.caption: Model of professional identity formation of undergraduate students in health promotion and prevention in Switzerland derived out of the focus group results.

claims.sentence: Data were collected using a semi-structured interview guideline with open ended questions (see Figure 1), developed by VB and AG based on Mancini’s theory on PI formation for university students [16].

Following their feedback, adaptations of the wording were made, and the guideline was finally structured in three parts: an introductory part, a main part that included theory-based core questions (see Figure 1), and an open end that enabled participants to add any comments or additional thoughts [62].
Summarizing the results on PI formation of undergraduate students in HP, we developed a model shown in Figure 2.
